WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.493 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.493 --> 00:02:39.680 align:middle line:90%


00:02:39.680 --> 00:02:43.250 align:middle line:90%
[HORN HONKING]

00:02:43.250 --> 00:02:46.730 align:middle line:84%
>> I bought my first van in the
summer of 2013 because I was

00:02:46.730 --> 00:02:48.830 align:middle line:84%
sick of wasting
money on hotel rooms.

00:02:48.830 --> 00:02:51.570 align:middle line:84%
In addition to being a
filmmaker, I'm also an author.

00:02:51.570 --> 00:02:54.920 align:middle line:84%
I've written several books,
and I used to go on book tours

00:02:54.920 --> 00:02:56.570 align:middle line:84%
all the time, which
basically means

00:02:56.570 --> 00:03:00.230 align:middle line:84%
that I would spend between 150
and 200 days a year traveling.

00:03:00.230 --> 00:03:02.620 align:middle line:84%
And it also means that I
used to spend between $15,000

00:03:02.620 --> 00:03:05.537 align:middle line:90%
and $20,000 on hotel stays.

00:03:05.537 --> 00:03:08.120 align:middle line:84%
Now, the worst part about it was
that I didn't really even get

00:03:08.120 --> 00:03:09.590 align:middle line:90%
to enjoy these hotel rooms.

00:03:09.590 --> 00:03:11.360 align:middle line:84%
I barely set foot
in them, actually.

00:03:11.360 --> 00:03:15.050 align:middle line:84%
Typically, how it would go
is I would go to town or city

00:03:15.050 --> 00:03:16.427 align:middle line:90%
and I would teach a class.

00:03:16.427 --> 00:03:17.510 align:middle line:90%
I would do a book signing.

00:03:17.510 --> 00:03:20.093 align:middle line:84%
And at the very end of the night
I'd go back to the hotel room

00:03:20.093 --> 00:03:22.860 align:middle line:84%
and I would just literally
throw my bones on the bed

00:03:22.860 --> 00:03:23.660 align:middle line:90%
and go to sleep.

00:03:23.660 --> 00:03:25.970 align:middle line:84%
Six hours later I'd wake
up, I'd get in the car

00:03:25.970 --> 00:03:27.540 align:middle line:90%
and go to the next location.

00:03:27.540 --> 00:03:28.800 align:middle line:90%
So this expense sucked.

00:03:28.800 --> 00:03:30.980 align:middle line:90%
It was 100% unnecessary.

00:03:30.980 --> 00:03:32.930 align:middle line:84%
And the rational
part of my brain

00:03:32.930 --> 00:03:34.700 align:middle line:84%
told me that something
had to change.

00:03:34.700 --> 00:03:36.350 align:middle line:84%
Prior to purchasing
a Sprinter van

00:03:36.350 --> 00:03:38.540 align:middle line:84%
I did quite a bit of
deliberating about which

00:03:38.540 --> 00:03:40.230 align:middle line:90%
vehicle would be best for me.

00:03:40.230 --> 00:03:42.410 align:middle line:84%
I needed a car that
was both volumous,

00:03:42.410 --> 00:03:45.560 align:middle line:84%
I needed a lot of room for
books and heavy film equipment,

00:03:45.560 --> 00:03:47.460 align:middle line:90%
but I also needed fuel economy.

00:03:47.460 --> 00:03:50.150 align:middle line:84%
I needed a car that I could
criss-cross the entire United

00:03:50.150 --> 00:03:54.680 align:middle line:84%
States in and I wouldn't just
get pillaged at the gas pump.

00:03:54.680 --> 00:03:57.650 align:middle line:84%
Initially, I had my eyes
set on a VW Euro van.

00:03:57.650 --> 00:03:59.600 align:middle line:84%
But after perusing
countless auto listings

00:03:59.600 --> 00:04:02.090 align:middle line:84%
I quickly learned that
a 20-year-old beat up

00:04:02.090 --> 00:04:05.090 align:middle line:84%
microbus with over
200,000 miles on it sells

00:04:05.090 --> 00:04:07.280 align:middle line:90%
for between 20 and 25 grand.

00:04:07.280 --> 00:04:08.810 align:middle line:84%
This seemed like a
ridiculous amount

00:04:08.810 --> 00:04:11.940 align:middle line:84%
to pay for an old van that
could fall apart at any moment.

00:04:11.940 --> 00:04:12.800 align:middle line:90%
So I kept looking.

00:04:12.800 --> 00:04:14.340 align:middle line:84%
I looked into other
options as well,

00:04:14.340 --> 00:04:17.600 align:middle line:84%
such as trucks and campers,
pull-behind trailers and RVs,

00:04:17.600 --> 00:04:20.149 align:middle line:84%
but was ultimately deterred
by high mileage, low fuel

00:04:20.149 --> 00:04:23.390 align:middle line:84%
economy, lack of reliability,
and or hefty price tags.

00:04:23.390 --> 00:04:24.770 align:middle line:84%
Then during a work
trip to Europe

00:04:24.770 --> 00:04:28.340 align:middle line:84%
I discovered the Sprinter
van, and boy, was it glorious.

00:04:28.340 --> 00:04:31.430 align:middle line:84%
There was nothing embarrassing
or shameful about this van

00:04:31.430 --> 00:04:32.340 align:middle line:90%
whatsoever.

00:04:32.340 --> 00:04:34.700 align:middle line:84%
It was spacious,
it was practical,

00:04:34.700 --> 00:04:36.380 align:middle line:90%
and yet it was somehow classy.

00:04:36.380 --> 00:04:37.940 align:middle line:90%
And I instantly wanted one.

00:04:37.940 --> 00:04:40.010 align:middle line:84%
So when I returned home
from my overseas trip,

00:04:40.010 --> 00:04:41.350 align:middle line:90%
I googled Sprinter van.

00:04:41.350 --> 00:04:44.690 align:middle line:84%
I went down to my local Mercedes
dealership and I bought one.

00:04:44.690 --> 00:04:46.310 align:middle line:84%
I remember feeling
extremely nervous

00:04:46.310 --> 00:04:48.980 align:middle line:84%
because I'd never bought a
new vehicle before, let alone

00:04:48.980 --> 00:04:51.350 align:middle line:90%
one with a $40,000 price tag.

00:04:51.350 --> 00:04:54.590 align:middle line:84%
But again, the money that I
was shucking out on hotel stays

00:04:54.590 --> 00:04:56.180 align:middle line:90%
helped justify the purchase.

00:04:56.180 --> 00:04:57.735 align:middle line:84%
I've owned my van
for five years,

00:04:57.735 --> 00:04:59.360 align:middle line:84%
and I'm proud to
report that I've never

00:04:59.360 --> 00:05:01.520 align:middle line:90%
had one ounce of regret.

00:05:01.520 --> 00:05:02.935 align:middle line:90%
There's been no buyer's remorse.

00:05:02.935 --> 00:05:04.310 align:middle line:84%
Out of all the
different vehicles

00:05:04.310 --> 00:05:05.870 align:middle line:84%
that I've owned in
the past, this van

00:05:05.870 --> 00:05:09.300 align:middle line:84%
is by far my favorite vehicle
and I absolutely love it.

00:05:09.300 --> 00:05:13.550 align:middle line:84%
I like to compare my van to the
transition from a T9 cell phone

00:05:13.550 --> 00:05:15.180 align:middle line:84%
to a cell phone with
a full keyboard.

00:05:15.180 --> 00:05:16.830 align:middle line:84%
So if you recall,
back in the day,

00:05:16.830 --> 00:05:18.710 align:middle line:84%
we used to have those
brick Nokia phones.

00:05:18.710 --> 00:05:21.950 align:middle line:84%
And on those phones you had
to hit each button three times

00:05:21.950 --> 00:05:23.390 align:middle line:90%
to get a desired letter.

00:05:23.390 --> 00:05:24.920 align:middle line:84%
So texting was a
pain in the butt.

00:05:24.920 --> 00:05:27.590 align:middle line:84%
And then we all got phones
with full keyboards, which

00:05:27.590 --> 00:05:29.950 align:middle line:84%
means that we could now
write text much quicker,

00:05:29.950 --> 00:05:32.330 align:middle line:90%
it was much more convenient.

00:05:32.330 --> 00:05:34.490 align:middle line:84%
Our minds were blown
and it was evident

00:05:34.490 --> 00:05:36.860 align:middle line:84%
that we're never going
back to the old ways.

00:05:36.860 --> 00:05:39.740 align:middle line:84%
It just seems archaic
now to do that, right?

00:05:39.740 --> 00:05:40.760 align:middle line:90%
Same thing with a van.

00:05:40.760 --> 00:05:42.770 align:middle line:84%
When you experience
firsthand what

00:05:42.770 --> 00:05:46.040 align:middle line:84%
it's like to be able to freely
move around in your vehicle,

00:05:46.040 --> 00:05:48.920 align:middle line:84%
to get up from the driver's
seat and then go into the back,

00:05:48.920 --> 00:05:50.960 align:middle line:84%
maybe when it's raining
or snowing outside,

00:05:50.960 --> 00:05:53.180 align:middle line:84%
and yet you're comfortable,
you're standing upright,

00:05:53.180 --> 00:05:56.070 align:middle line:84%
you're warm and cozy, this
is an incredible feeling.

00:05:56.070 --> 00:05:58.400 align:middle line:84%
And you just can't replicate
it in other vehicles.

00:05:58.400 --> 00:06:00.710 align:middle line:84%
So once you experience the
comfort and the convenience

00:06:00.710 --> 00:06:04.370 align:middle line:84%
of the van you can't go back
to a sedan or a station wagon.

00:06:04.370 --> 00:06:05.600 align:middle line:90%
It's just not happening.

00:06:05.600 --> 00:06:07.940 align:middle line:84%
It goes without saying
that paying for hotel rooms

00:06:07.940 --> 00:06:09.440 align:middle line:84%
is now a thing of
the past for me.

00:06:09.440 --> 00:06:12.470 align:middle line:84%
Now when I travel I stay in
my vehicle, and in doing this

00:06:12.470 --> 00:06:13.467 align:middle line:90%
I save heaps of dough.

00:06:13.467 --> 00:06:15.050 align:middle line:84%
And I'm way more
comfortable because I

00:06:15.050 --> 00:06:17.910 align:middle line:84%
get to sleep in my own bed
surrounded by my own smells

00:06:17.910 --> 00:06:18.710 align:middle line:90%
every night.

00:06:18.710 --> 00:06:20.600 align:middle line:84%
In addition to being
great work vehicles,

00:06:20.600 --> 00:06:22.507 align:middle line:84%
vans are also
fantastic for leisure.

00:06:22.507 --> 00:06:24.590 align:middle line:84%
Whether you're going
adventuring with your buddies

00:06:24.590 --> 00:06:27.950 align:middle line:84%
or visiting relatives in another
town, traveling by way of van

00:06:27.950 --> 00:06:30.560 align:middle line:84%
allows you to be more
spontaneous, more flexible,

00:06:30.560 --> 00:06:31.970 align:middle line:90%
self-reliant, and free.

00:06:31.970 --> 00:06:33.950 align:middle line:84%
Presently I don't live
in my van full time.

00:06:33.950 --> 00:06:35.360 align:middle line:90%
I use it more like a weekender.

00:06:35.360 --> 00:06:36.720 align:middle line:90%
So my girlfriend has a house.

00:06:36.720 --> 00:06:37.520 align:middle line:90%
I live there.

00:06:37.520 --> 00:06:41.030 align:middle line:84%
And then whenever we want to go
adventuring, we fill up the van

00:06:41.030 --> 00:06:42.020 align:middle line:90%
and we go.

00:06:42.020 --> 00:06:45.080 align:middle line:84%
Whether that be for a weekend,
or a week, or a month,

00:06:45.080 --> 00:06:46.423 align:middle line:90%
this works really well for us.

00:06:46.423 --> 00:06:47.840 align:middle line:84%
And so we'd like
to think about it

00:06:47.840 --> 00:06:49.760 align:middle line:84%
kind of like in
spaceship terms, where

00:06:49.760 --> 00:06:52.430 align:middle line:84%
the house is the mothership
and the van is the rocket.

00:06:52.430 --> 00:06:55.610 align:middle line:84%
And every so often the van has
to resupply like rockets do,

00:06:55.610 --> 00:06:58.550 align:middle line:84%
and then we fly off somewhere
else, and go exploring,

00:06:58.550 --> 00:07:00.350 align:middle line:84%
go have fun, go
to work, whatever.

00:07:00.350 --> 00:07:02.690 align:middle line:84%
During the first couple
years of van ownership,

00:07:02.690 --> 00:07:04.460 align:middle line:84%
one thing that I
remember very distinctly

00:07:04.460 --> 00:07:07.010 align:middle line:84%
is that people used to
stop me on the street.

00:07:07.010 --> 00:07:08.863 align:middle line:84%
Random strangers would
stop me on the street

00:07:08.863 --> 00:07:11.030 align:middle line:84%
and they'd ask me a plethora
of different questions.

00:07:11.030 --> 00:07:13.550 align:middle line:84%
They would ask me things like,
what kind of van is that?

00:07:13.550 --> 00:07:14.900 align:middle line:90%
Do you like your van?

00:07:14.900 --> 00:07:16.670 align:middle line:84%
What kind of gas
mileage do you get?

00:07:16.670 --> 00:07:17.660 align:middle line:90%
Where do you get it?

00:07:17.660 --> 00:07:18.850 align:middle line:90%
How much was it?

00:07:18.850 --> 00:07:20.090 align:middle line:90%
Et cetera, et cetera.

00:07:20.090 --> 00:07:22.100 align:middle line:84%
And then one day all
the questions stopped.

00:07:22.100 --> 00:07:24.770 align:middle line:84%
And people just stopped
coming up to me, period.

00:07:24.770 --> 00:07:27.050 align:middle line:84%
And it was kind of strange
because it happened

00:07:27.050 --> 00:07:28.890 align:middle line:90%
consistently, and then boom.

00:07:28.890 --> 00:07:29.690 align:middle line:90%
Nothing.

00:07:29.690 --> 00:07:31.148 align:middle line:84%
After pondering on
this for a while

00:07:31.148 --> 00:07:33.278 align:middle line:84%
I figured that the shift
had to do with the fact

00:07:33.278 --> 00:07:34.820 align:middle line:84%
that there are more
vans on the road.

00:07:34.820 --> 00:07:36.487 align:middle line:84%
While vans and van
life have been around

00:07:36.487 --> 00:07:38.360 align:middle line:84%
since the early '60s,
we are currently

00:07:38.360 --> 00:07:41.600 align:middle line:84%
seeing one of the biggest van
booms in history right now.

00:07:41.600 --> 00:07:43.750 align:middle line:90%
[CHEERING]

00:07:43.750 --> 00:07:45.940 align:middle line:84%
If you look at commercial
vans sales in America

00:07:45.940 --> 00:07:50.730 align:middle line:84%
alone since about 2016, you'll
notice that Ford Transits,

00:07:50.730 --> 00:07:52.030 align:middle line:90%
they're the leaders in the US.

00:07:52.030 --> 00:07:54.400 align:middle line:84%
They sell about
14,000 vans a month.

00:07:54.400 --> 00:07:57.370 align:middle line:84%
Chevy Express sells
6,000 vans a month.

00:07:57.370 --> 00:07:59.950 align:middle line:90%
Ford E-Series, 5.8.

00:07:59.950 --> 00:08:03.130 align:middle line:84%
Dodge pro master is
next at 3.3 thousand.

00:08:03.130 --> 00:08:06.220 align:middle line:84%
Mercedes Benz is
close behind at 3,000,

00:08:06.220 --> 00:08:10.240 align:middle line:84%
and the Nissan NV Series
sells about 1.7 thousand vans

00:08:10.240 --> 00:08:11.240 align:middle line:90%
per month.

00:08:11.240 --> 00:08:14.350 align:middle line:84%
So that's roughly 33,000
vans per month total,

00:08:14.350 --> 00:08:18.100 align:middle line:84%
and 405,000 vans per
year in the US alone.

00:08:18.100 --> 00:08:22.660 align:middle line:84%
I'm no expert, but 405,000
new vans on the road per year

00:08:22.660 --> 00:08:23.920 align:middle line:90%
seems like a lot of vans.

00:08:23.920 --> 00:08:26.980 align:middle line:84%
Maybe that's why it feels like
vans are everywhere these days,

00:08:26.980 --> 00:08:28.330 align:middle line:90%
because they literally are.

00:08:28.330 --> 00:08:30.520 align:middle line:84%
Globally, vans appear
to be trending as well.

00:08:30.520 --> 00:08:33.280 align:middle line:84%
In the first half of
2017 Mercedes Benz

00:08:33.280 --> 00:08:35.890 align:middle line:84%
reported that it sold
nearly 200,000 vans,

00:08:35.890 --> 00:08:38.692 align:middle line:84%
mainly Sprinters and
Metris's worldwide.

00:08:38.692 --> 00:08:40.150 align:middle line:84%
This marked the
fifth year in a row

00:08:40.150 --> 00:08:42.669 align:middle line:84%
that their van division
experienced significant growth.

00:08:42.669 --> 00:08:44.230 align:middle line:84%
And according to
expert projections,

00:08:44.230 --> 00:08:46.540 align:middle line:84%
this trend will only
continue to increase.

00:08:46.540 --> 00:08:48.160 align:middle line:84%
In addition to
these sales figures,

00:08:48.160 --> 00:08:51.370 align:middle line:84%
today there's way more resources
about vans and van life

00:08:51.370 --> 00:08:52.520 align:middle line:90%
than ever before.

00:08:52.520 --> 00:08:55.810 align:middle line:84%
There are literally
countless blogs and websites

00:08:55.810 --> 00:08:59.500 align:middle line:84%
and social media accounts and
YouTube videos about vans.

00:08:59.500 --> 00:09:01.090 align:middle line:84%
And so people have
a lot more ways

00:09:01.090 --> 00:09:02.920 align:middle line:84%
that they can learn
about van life, which

00:09:02.920 --> 00:09:05.410 align:middle line:84%
means they no
longer have to stop

00:09:05.410 --> 00:09:07.660 align:middle line:84%
random strangers on
the street like myself

00:09:07.660 --> 00:09:09.460 align:middle line:84%
and get information
directly from them.

00:09:09.460 --> 00:09:10.750 align:middle line:90%
So what is this all about?

00:09:10.750 --> 00:09:12.130 align:middle line:90%
Why are vans booming?

00:09:12.130 --> 00:09:13.720 align:middle line:84%
Clearly there is
a need out there

00:09:13.720 --> 00:09:15.340 align:middle line:90%
that these vehicles are meeting.

00:09:15.340 --> 00:09:18.110 align:middle line:84%
And yet the answer to
this is anybody's guess.

00:09:18.110 --> 00:09:20.428 align:middle line:84%
In fact, even Mercedes
Benz has no idea.

00:09:20.428 --> 00:09:21.970 align:middle line:84%
And I know this
because they actually

00:09:21.970 --> 00:09:24.010 align:middle line:84%
sent me an email where
they said, "Sergei,

00:09:24.010 --> 00:09:25.890 align:middle line:84%
why is it that you
think vans are booming?"

00:09:25.890 --> 00:09:28.750 align:middle line:84%
So, you know, when they're
asking somebody like myself,

00:09:28.750 --> 00:09:31.810 align:middle line:84%
I can only assume that they
have questions as to why this is

00:09:31.810 --> 00:09:33.250 align:middle line:90%
happening and what's going on.

00:09:33.250 --> 00:09:36.370 align:middle line:84%
Major publications such as "The
New Yorker," "Time," and "Vice"

00:09:36.370 --> 00:09:37.780 align:middle line:90%
have their own speculations.

00:09:37.780 --> 00:09:39.580 align:middle line:84%
In one way or another
they all claim

00:09:39.580 --> 00:09:43.000 align:middle line:84%
vans are trending because van
life is the new American dream.

00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:44.660 align:middle line:84%
This intrigues me
for several reasons.

00:09:44.660 --> 00:09:46.630 align:middle line:84%
Number one, it's a
big bold statement

00:09:46.630 --> 00:09:48.370 align:middle line:84%
that I automatically
want to challenge.

00:09:48.370 --> 00:09:50.860 align:middle line:84%
And number two, it very
well might be true.

00:09:50.860 --> 00:09:53.170 align:middle line:84%
Is van life really the
next American dream?

00:09:53.170 --> 00:09:54.700 align:middle line:90%
If so, then why?

00:09:54.700 --> 00:09:56.410 align:middle line:84%
Are people moving
into vans because they

00:09:56.410 --> 00:09:58.930 align:middle line:84%
can no longer afford to
live in traditional houses?

00:09:58.930 --> 00:10:01.240 align:middle line:84%
Or are they simply
shifting their values

00:10:01.240 --> 00:10:03.910 align:middle line:84%
because they're finding that
alternative lifestyles make

00:10:03.910 --> 00:10:05.630 align:middle line:90%
them more fulfilled and happy?

00:10:05.630 --> 00:10:07.220 align:middle line:90%
Maybe that's what's going on.

00:10:07.220 --> 00:10:09.430 align:middle line:84%
If this is the case,
does van living

00:10:09.430 --> 00:10:12.070 align:middle line:84%
actually make people
more happy and fulfilled?

00:10:12.070 --> 00:10:13.960 align:middle line:90%
Is this a sustainable lifestyle?

00:10:13.960 --> 00:10:16.960 align:middle line:84%
I want to know if van life is
a trend that will someday pass

00:10:16.960 --> 00:10:20.200 align:middle line:84%
and we'll think, "Oh my
god, I can't believe we ever

00:10:20.200 --> 00:10:21.970 align:middle line:84%
thought this was
cool," or perhaps this

00:10:21.970 --> 00:10:23.890 align:middle line:84%
is a viable lifestyle
that's here to stay.

00:10:23.890 --> 00:10:25.810 align:middle line:84%
I've decided to act
on this curiosity

00:10:25.810 --> 00:10:28.420 align:middle line:84%
and make a movie that
investigates this fan boom.

00:10:28.420 --> 00:10:30.700 align:middle line:84%
This summer I'm going to
jump into my Sprinter van,

00:10:30.700 --> 00:10:32.560 align:middle line:84%
and I'm going to go
wherever the wind blows

00:10:32.560 --> 00:10:35.050 align:middle line:84%
me to try and interview
as many different people

00:10:35.050 --> 00:10:38.950 align:middle line:84%
as I can that are in some way,
shape, or form tied to vans.

00:10:38.950 --> 00:10:41.330 align:middle line:84%
I want to sit down with as
many different demographics

00:10:41.330 --> 00:10:42.130 align:middle line:90%
as I can.

00:10:42.130 --> 00:10:45.220 align:middle line:84%
This being young couples,
