00:33:48.370 --> 00:33:50.823 align:middle line:84%
So when you're making
breakfast in nature,

00:33:50.823 --> 00:33:52.240 align:middle line:84%
you always want
to look around you

00:33:52.240 --> 00:33:55.550 align:middle line:84%
because you might just find
some wild growing vegetables.

00:33:55.550 --> 00:33:57.100 align:middle line:90%
This right here is wild onion.

00:33:57.100 --> 00:33:59.770 align:middle line:84%
The easiest way to identify
an onion is by the smell.

00:33:59.770 --> 00:34:02.680 align:middle line:84%
All onions smell the same,
just like a store bought onion.

00:34:02.680 --> 00:34:05.320 align:middle line:84%
And today we're just going to
harvest a few for our meal.

00:34:05.320 --> 00:34:07.180 align:middle line:84%
And we're only going
to harvest the top.

00:34:07.180 --> 00:34:09.159 align:middle line:84%
We're going to leave the
roots intact so as not

00:34:09.159 --> 00:34:10.810 align:middle line:90%
to disturb the plant too much.

00:34:10.810 --> 00:34:12.429 align:middle line:84%
The seeds and fruits
of a plant are

00:34:12.429 --> 00:34:15.429 align:middle line:84%
nature's gift to the creature,
to the animal, to the human.

00:34:15.429 --> 00:34:18.040 align:middle line:84%
And so it's OK to take a
couple, throw them in your meal.

00:34:18.040 --> 00:34:20.050 align:middle line:84%
And it also makes your
meal more nutritious

00:34:20.050 --> 00:34:23.800 align:middle line:84%
because they grow in topsoil
that hasn't been depleted.

00:34:23.800 --> 00:34:25.719 align:middle line:84%
Their root systems
are longer, so they're

00:34:25.719 --> 00:34:27.699 align:middle line:90%
like nature's super food.

00:34:27.699 --> 00:34:28.659 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:34:28.659 --> 00:34:29.830 align:middle line:90%
Update time.

00:34:29.830 --> 00:34:31.690 align:middle line:84%
So Kyleigh and I are
driving in the van.

00:34:31.690 --> 00:34:33.550 align:middle line:84%
We're heading to the
VanLife Diaries van

00:34:33.550 --> 00:34:35.590 align:middle line:90%
festival in Victor, Idaho.

00:34:35.590 --> 00:34:39.100 align:middle line:84%
But I've been texting on the
phone with Dave and Diane

00:34:39.100 --> 00:34:41.179 align:middle line:90%
from Aluminess this entire time.

00:34:41.179 --> 00:34:42.947 align:middle line:84%
And they just agreed
to sit down with me

00:34:42.947 --> 00:34:43.989 align:middle line:90%
and give me an interview.

00:34:43.989 --> 00:34:47.400 align:middle line:84%
So what this means is we
have to divert a little bit.

00:34:47.400 --> 00:34:50.000 align:middle line:84%
And by a little bit, I
mean like 300 to 500 miles

00:34:50.000 --> 00:34:50.800 align:middle line:90%
out of our way.

00:34:50.800 --> 00:34:52.389 align:middle line:84%
If you're not familiar
with Aluminess,

00:34:52.389 --> 00:34:55.840 align:middle line:84%
they are a premium company that
manufactures racks and ladders

00:34:55.840 --> 00:34:58.030 align:middle line:84%
for trucks and vans Dave
and Diane have been doing

00:34:58.030 --> 00:34:59.330 align:middle line:90%
this for many, many years.

00:34:59.330 --> 00:35:01.900 align:middle line:84%
They know all the ins
and outs of van life.

00:35:01.900 --> 00:35:04.270 align:middle line:84%
And this is an opportunity
that I just can't pass up.

00:35:04.270 --> 00:35:07.420 align:middle line:84%
So this means that we
are probably not going

00:35:07.420 --> 00:35:09.520 align:middle line:84%
to be sleeping much in
the next couple days,

00:35:09.520 --> 00:35:12.100 align:middle line:84%
because we now have to veer
north to Coeur d'Alene, which

00:35:12.100 --> 00:35:14.410 align:middle line:84%
is a few hundred
miles out of our way.

00:35:14.410 --> 00:35:16.030 align:middle line:84%
Then we're going to
have to veer south

00:35:16.030 --> 00:35:18.070 align:middle line:84%
back to our original
destination, which

00:35:18.070 --> 00:35:18.968 align:middle line:90%
is Victor, Idaho.

00:35:18.968 --> 00:35:21.010 align:middle line:84%
But you know what, I don't
even care because this

00:35:21.010 --> 00:35:23.390 align:middle line:90%
is an incredible opportunity.

00:35:23.390 --> 00:35:25.780 align:middle line:84%
And I just didn't
think I'd get it.

00:35:25.780 --> 00:35:26.740 align:middle line:90%
Whoo!

00:35:26.740 --> 00:35:28.990 align:middle line:90%
I'm excited.

00:35:28.990 --> 00:35:31.280 align:middle line:84%
>> So you want to know a
little bit about the van life

00:35:31.280 --> 00:35:33.940 align:middle line:84%
and stuff, so I thought I'd
take you back to what I think is

00:35:33.940 --> 00:35:36.160 align:middle line:84%
kind of at least a
decent starting point.

00:35:36.160 --> 00:35:38.240 align:middle line:84%
And that is the
Volkswagen camper van.

00:35:38.240 --> 00:35:39.940 align:middle line:84%
And so that was
around for people

00:35:39.940 --> 00:35:43.260 align:middle line:84%
to actually go camp in a van
way back in the '60s, I believe.

00:35:43.260 --> 00:35:46.120 align:middle line:84%
I'm not sure exactly
the first year.

00:35:46.120 --> 00:35:49.450 align:middle line:84%
But a gentleman,
Charles and his dad

00:35:49.450 --> 00:35:52.030 align:middle line:84%
started a company
called Sportsmobile in I

00:35:52.030 --> 00:35:52.970 align:middle line:90%
believe Austin, Texas.

00:35:52.970 --> 00:35:54.790 align:middle line:84%
They always had a
shop in Indiana,

00:35:54.790 --> 00:35:57.550 align:middle line:84%
and they scaled way
up with Volkswagen.

00:35:57.550 --> 00:35:59.820 align:middle line:84%
And then West Valley
came on the picture,

00:35:59.820 --> 00:36:00.820 align:middle line:90%
or was on there as well.

00:36:00.820 --> 00:36:04.940 align:middle line:84%
And then they started doing
Ford, Chevy, Dodge, and so on.

00:36:04.940 --> 00:36:07.840 align:middle line:84%
So that was kind of where the
whole van thing originally

00:36:07.840 --> 00:36:09.490 align:middle line:90%
was, in my mind, started.

00:36:09.490 --> 00:36:15.010 align:middle line:84%
And then in about, till
'91 or '92, a gentleman,

00:36:15.010 --> 00:36:18.920 align:middle line:84%
Alan Feld, who actually
owns Sportsmobile West,

00:36:18.920 --> 00:36:22.450 align:middle line:84%
he'd worked for me when he was
20 years old in a stockroom

00:36:22.450 --> 00:36:24.350 align:middle line:90%
at a medical device company.

00:36:24.350 --> 00:36:27.330 align:middle line:84%
And he went on to do some
other things beyond that.

00:36:27.330 --> 00:36:29.710 align:middle line:84%
And one was sales, and he ran
into a Sportsmobile, which

00:36:29.710 --> 00:36:32.660 align:middle line:84%
was a van converted to a motor
home, a Class B motor home,

00:36:32.660 --> 00:36:33.460 align:middle line:90%
they call them.

00:36:33.460 --> 00:36:34.460 align:middle line:90%
And he felt he wanted one.

00:36:34.460 --> 00:36:36.610 align:middle line:84%
And he found out he had
to go to Texas to get one.

00:36:36.610 --> 00:36:38.920 align:middle line:84%
And so he thought
it'd be a great idea

00:36:38.920 --> 00:36:41.470 align:middle line:84%
to do a franchise or
something in California.

00:36:41.470 --> 00:36:44.140 align:middle line:84%
And Charles, who was the one
who started that or owned it

00:36:44.140 --> 00:36:46.580 align:middle line:90%
at the time, was not interested.

00:36:46.580 --> 00:36:47.955 align:middle line:84%
Didn't want to
scale up again, he

00:36:47.955 --> 00:36:49.240 align:middle line:84%
didn't want anything to
do with another business.

00:36:49.240 --> 00:36:51.670 align:middle line:84%
Would just like to have
his little shop down there

00:36:51.670 --> 00:36:53.628 align:middle line:84%
and build four or five
a month and that was it.

00:36:53.628 --> 00:36:56.170 align:middle line:84%
And so Alan asked me to go with
him down there to talk to him

00:36:56.170 --> 00:36:57.660 align:middle line:84%
and see if we could
talk him into it.

00:36:57.660 --> 00:36:59.535 align:middle line:84%
So we grabbed on a plane
and went down there.

00:36:59.535 --> 00:37:02.800 align:middle line:84%
And Charles changed his tone
after talking both of us,

00:37:02.800 --> 00:37:07.120 align:middle line:84%
and said OK and
gave us a go ahead.

00:37:07.120 --> 00:37:09.910 align:middle line:84%
I chose not to do it with Alan,
mainly because I didn't want

00:37:09.910 --> 00:37:11.390 align:middle line:90%
to lose a friend over stuff.

00:37:11.390 --> 00:37:14.470 align:middle line:84%
And I'd done a big business for
a group of open heart surgeons

00:37:14.470 --> 00:37:16.300 align:middle line:84%
that, you know, just
don't want to get

00:37:16.300 --> 00:37:17.780 align:middle line:90%
involved in that kind of stuff.

00:37:17.780 --> 00:37:20.710 align:middle line:84%
So anyway, over the years
Alan basically started

00:37:20.710 --> 00:37:23.470 align:middle line:84%
making these vans out
of Chevys and Fords.

00:37:23.470 --> 00:37:27.190 align:middle line:84%
And then he started looking
more at the younger people.

00:37:27.190 --> 00:37:29.110 align:middle line:84%
Prior to that it was
kind of retirement van.

00:37:29.110 --> 00:37:30.550 align:middle line:84%
People would retire,
get one of these,

00:37:30.550 --> 00:37:33.008 align:middle line:84%
go see the national parks, stay
in a hotel once in a while.

00:37:33.008 --> 00:37:34.835 align:middle line:90%
But they had some camping and--

00:37:34.835 --> 00:37:36.960 align:middle line:84%
small camping capability,
but not a big motor home.

00:37:36.960 --> 00:37:39.430 align:middle line:84%
So Alan started putting
the big tires on.

00:37:39.430 --> 00:37:42.330 align:middle line:84%
And hey, you can go out in
the back country and so on.

00:37:42.330 --> 00:37:44.290 align:middle line:84%
And then he got a company
called Quigley Motor

00:37:44.290 --> 00:37:46.550 align:middle line:84%
Company to convert some
to four wheel drive.

00:37:46.550 --> 00:37:48.940 align:middle line:84%
Quigley Motor Company's back
in Manchester, Pennsylvania.

00:37:48.940 --> 00:37:51.467 align:middle line:84%
And so they started making
him four wheel drives for him,

00:37:51.467 --> 00:37:53.300 align:middle line:84%
send him out an empty
van, four wheel drive.

00:37:53.300 --> 00:37:56.348 align:middle line:84%
He'd convert it to the
whole pop top version

00:37:56.348 --> 00:37:57.640 align:middle line:90%
like the one you saw out front.

00:37:57.640 --> 00:37:59.770 align:middle line:84%
And then after about two
years, all of a sudden

00:37:59.770 --> 00:38:01.270 align:middle line:84%
there was a problem
with four wheel drive.

00:38:01.270 --> 00:38:02.530 align:middle line:84%
The front ends
were all worn out.

00:38:02.530 --> 00:38:04.120 align:middle line:84%
They were shaking, they
were causing problems,

00:38:04.120 --> 00:38:05.650 align:middle line:84%
brakes were
squeaking, and so on.

00:38:05.650 --> 00:38:08.210 align:middle line:84%
And they argued back and
forth about the problem,

00:38:08.210 --> 00:38:10.210 align:middle line:84%
whose problem it was, and
who's going to fix it.

00:38:10.210 --> 00:38:12.953 align:middle line:84%
And actually Quigley, Mike
Quigley back east canceled

00:38:12.953 --> 00:38:14.620 align:middle line:84%
all the warranties
on all the customers,

00:38:14.620 --> 00:38:15.618 align:middle line:90%
sent them all a letter.

00:38:15.618 --> 00:38:17.160 align:middle line:84%
Alan happened to
call me up because I

00:38:17.160 --> 00:38:18.970 align:middle line:84%
build the street rods, and said,
"Just tell me how to fix it."

00:38:18.970 --> 00:38:20.887 align:middle line:84%
He's really good on the
marketing and customer

00:38:20.887 --> 00:38:22.190 align:middle line:90%
service and sales and so on.

00:38:22.190 --> 00:38:24.250 align:middle line:84%
But I'm kind of the
nuts and bolts nut.

00:38:24.250 --> 00:38:26.150 align:middle line:84%
And so I went up there
and took some apart,

00:38:26.150 --> 00:38:28.120 align:middle line:84%
flew back east, worked
with Mike Quigley.

00:38:28.120 --> 00:38:30.320 align:middle line:84%
We redesigned the
front end and so on.

00:38:30.320 --> 00:38:33.340 align:middle line:84%
But one of the issues was
they were putting these steel

00:38:33.340 --> 00:38:35.262 align:middle line:84%
bumpers that were
mainly used on farms

00:38:35.262 --> 00:38:37.595 align:middle line:84%
for pushing combines and stuff
around, that weighed 300,

00:38:37.595 --> 00:38:39.190 align:middle line:90%
400 pounds.

00:38:39.190 --> 00:38:44.710 align:middle line:84%
And the guy's doing 15, 30
miles an hour kind of thing.

00:38:44.710 --> 00:38:47.380 align:middle line:84%
And so they were tearing
up the front end as well as

00:38:47.380 --> 00:38:49.000 align:middle line:90%
some other issues that we saw.

00:38:49.000 --> 00:38:51.670 align:middle line:84%
So I tried to get his suppliers
to make them out of aluminum.

00:38:51.670 --> 00:38:53.950 align:middle line:84%
They were quite
rude about what type

00:38:53.950 --> 00:38:57.160 align:middle line:84%
of less than intelligent
person would make something out

00:38:57.160 --> 00:38:58.070 align:middle line:90%
of aluminum.

00:38:58.070 --> 00:39:00.850 align:middle line:84%
If you wanted a beer can
or Japanese pop metal,

00:39:00.850 --> 00:39:02.200 align:middle line:90%
go see Coors or Budweiser.

00:39:02.200 --> 00:39:04.150 align:middle line:84%
So next thing you know
I'm in my driveway

00:39:04.150 --> 00:39:06.150 align:middle line:84%
with a sheet of aluminum
and a saw and a welder,

00:39:06.150 --> 00:39:08.647 align:middle line:84%
and I'm mumbling
about those guys.

00:39:08.647 --> 00:39:10.480 align:middle line:84%
Because I'm trying to
tell them that fighter

00:39:10.480 --> 00:39:12.367 align:middle line:84%
jets land at full
throttle on a carrier,

00:39:12.367 --> 00:39:13.700 align:middle line:90%
and that's lightweight material.

00:39:13.700 --> 00:39:14.660 align:middle line:90%
It's all about design.

00:39:14.660 --> 00:39:17.260 align:middle line:84%
And so I made some
and took it up.

00:39:17.260 --> 00:39:18.733 align:middle line:90%
And Sportsmobile liked it.

00:39:18.733 --> 00:39:20.650 align:middle line:84%
I was retired at the
time, so I could do that.

00:39:20.650 --> 00:39:23.213 align:middle line:84%
And then I went and
found a guy down

00:39:23.213 --> 00:39:25.630 align:middle line:84%
on the boat docks that could
weld way better than I could,

00:39:25.630 --> 00:39:27.463 align:middle line:84%
manipulate aluminum a
lot better than I did.

00:39:27.463 --> 00:39:30.173 align:middle line:84%
And so I just would buy all
the material, take it to him,

00:39:30.173 --> 00:39:31.090 align:middle line:90%
all cut out and so on.

00:39:31.090 --> 00:39:33.550 align:middle line:84%
He'd weld them up, I'd take them
up to Fresno from San Diego,

00:39:33.550 --> 00:39:34.090 align:middle line:90%
drop them off.

00:39:34.090 --> 00:39:35.470 align:middle line:84%
And then after
that it just grew.

00:39:35.470 --> 00:39:37.720 align:middle line:84%
And then I just started
adding more items.

00:39:37.720 --> 00:39:40.180 align:middle line:84%
Nerf bars, rear
bumpers, roof racks,

00:39:40.180 --> 00:39:41.540 align:middle line:90%
ladders, that kind of thing.

00:39:41.540 --> 00:39:43.390 align:middle line:84%
We started building
these things actually

00:39:43.390 --> 00:39:46.360 align:middle line:84%
in the parking lot of sports
fishing company with one guy,

00:39:46.360 --> 00:39:50.150 align:middle line:84%
and then I got 800 square feet,
then 1,000, then 2,000, 3,000,

00:39:50.150 --> 00:39:51.080 align:middle line:90%
5,000, 10,000.

00:39:51.080 --> 00:39:52.690 align:middle line:90%
We're up to 30,000 feet now.

00:39:52.690 --> 00:39:57.160 align:middle line:84%
And you know, we bring
people on and teach them

00:39:57.160 --> 00:39:58.840 align:middle line:90%
how we want to do the product.

00:39:58.840 --> 00:40:03.310 align:middle line:84%
We design it for the features
and benefits that we think,

00:40:03.310 --> 00:40:05.820 align:middle line:84%
or that we get feedback
from our customers.

00:40:05.820 --> 00:40:08.270 align:middle line:84%
Many of our customers are
depicted in these drawings

00:40:08.270 --> 00:40:09.070 align:middle line:90%
here.

00:40:09.070 --> 00:40:10.300 align:middle line:90%
They're pioneers.

00:40:10.300 --> 00:40:13.163 align:middle line:84%
They find out a way to break it
or something that doesn't do,

00:40:13.163 --> 00:40:14.830 align:middle line:84%
and they get a few
errors in their back.

00:40:14.830 --> 00:40:17.800 align:middle line:84%
And so we invite them back in
and we replace it or fix it

00:40:17.800 --> 00:40:20.260 align:middle line:90%
or evolve it.

00:40:20.260 --> 00:40:24.520 align:middle line:84%
So that's kind of our
philosophy is to try and make

00:40:24.520 --> 00:40:25.790 align:middle line:90%
the best product out there.

00:40:25.790 --> 00:40:28.530 align:middle line:84%
And the reason for the aluminum
is one, it's lightweight,

00:40:28.530 --> 00:40:30.770 align:middle line:84%
so it doesn't take
up the suspension

00:40:30.770 --> 00:40:32.520 align:middle line:84%
that you need when
you're going off road.

00:40:32.520 --> 00:40:34.670 align:middle line:84%
Whereas if you compress
that suspension,

00:40:34.670 --> 00:40:36.890 align:middle line:84%
you're back to zero even
if you spend a lot of money

00:40:36.890 --> 00:40:37.830 align:middle line:90%
to improve it.

00:40:37.830 --> 00:40:38.630 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:40:38.630 --> 00:40:40.180 align:middle line:90%
Now you're on the hot seat.

00:40:40.180 --> 00:40:41.420 align:middle line:90%
Why are vans booming?

00:40:41.420 --> 00:40:42.500 align:middle line:90%
What's your assessment?

00:40:42.500 --> 00:40:44.720 align:middle line:84%
>> The new vans, one,
are much more efficient.

00:40:44.720 --> 00:40:47.750 align:middle line:84%
So they can get up in the
area of 20 miles per gallon.

00:40:47.750 --> 00:40:49.620 align:middle line:90%
They have a lot more room.

00:40:49.620 --> 00:40:51.140 align:middle line:90%
They have a lot more features.

00:40:51.140 --> 00:40:54.140 align:middle line:84%
Whereas the previous vans
were very, pretty tight.

00:40:54.140 --> 00:40:55.970 align:middle line:84%
And when you get
two people in those

00:40:55.970 --> 00:40:58.080 align:middle line:84%
there's not much room
to get around and so on.

00:40:58.080 --> 00:41:00.435 align:middle line:84%
But in the Sprinter van and
the Transit van and stuff

00:41:00.435 --> 00:41:02.810 align:middle line:84%
you get different lengths, so
you can get a lot more gear

00:41:02.810 --> 00:41:03.290 align:middle line:90%
in there.

00:41:03.290 --> 00:41:06.140 align:middle line:84%
And people are wanting to take
