you come into the van and you
have like so many decisions

01:21:17.340 --> 01:21:18.570 align:middle line:90%
that you have to make.

01:21:18.570 --> 01:21:21.330 align:middle line:90%
That can be hard for people.

01:21:21.330 --> 01:21:25.260 align:middle line:84%
And I think you're
not always staying

01:21:25.260 --> 01:21:26.700 align:middle line:90%
at a beautiful campsite.

01:21:26.700 --> 01:21:28.390 align:middle line:84%
A lot of times
you're staying either

01:21:28.390 --> 01:21:32.760 align:middle line:84%
at a campground or a Walmart,
or on the side of the road.

01:21:32.760 --> 01:21:35.400 align:middle line:84%
And it's not necessarily what
people show on Instagram,

01:21:35.400 --> 01:21:36.730 align:middle line:90%
these beautiful camp sites.

01:21:36.730 --> 01:21:37.660 align:middle line:90%
There's some of that.

01:21:37.660 --> 01:21:40.020 align:middle line:84%
But there's also, like,
not beautiful camp sites.

01:21:40.020 --> 01:21:43.080 align:middle line:84%
And I think sometimes people
have these expectations

01:21:43.080 --> 01:21:44.760 align:middle line:84%
about like what van
life's going to be,

01:21:44.760 --> 01:21:46.677 align:middle line:84%
and that everyday is
going to be like the most

01:21:46.677 --> 01:21:49.880 align:middle line:84%
exciting day of your life,
where there's a lot of mundane.

01:21:49.880 --> 01:21:51.900 align:middle line:84%
Also, you spend a
lot of time driving,

01:21:51.900 --> 01:21:54.600 align:middle line:84%
you spend a lot of time
looking for good campsites.

01:21:54.600 --> 01:21:59.280 align:middle line:84%
And so I think some people like
the challenges that come with

01:21:59.280 --> 01:22:02.205 align:middle line:84%
it and thrive in those
environments and others don't.

01:22:02.205 --> 01:22:04.095 align:middle line:90%
And so then that sort of--

01:22:04.095 --> 01:22:07.470 align:middle line:84%
in the face of those
challenges it causes stress,

01:22:07.470 --> 01:22:09.670 align:middle line:84%
and that's not the
point of being out here.

01:22:09.670 --> 01:22:12.210 align:middle line:84%
If you get in a van and
all you are stressed then

01:22:12.210 --> 01:22:16.470 align:middle line:90%
that's not really fun.

01:22:16.470 --> 01:22:19.590 align:middle line:84%
>> One thing that I just
thought of as you were talking,

01:22:19.590 --> 01:22:24.570 align:middle line:84%
so maybe part of the Instagram
appeal is this carefree life.

01:22:24.570 --> 01:22:27.030 align:middle line:84%
And then when you get in a van
you realize, well, you know,

01:22:27.030 --> 01:22:28.770 align:middle line:90%
life is still not problem-free.

01:22:28.770 --> 01:22:31.950 align:middle line:84%
You have to find water,
you have to find a place

01:22:31.950 --> 01:22:32.992 align:middle line:90%
to bunk up for the night.

01:22:32.992 --> 01:22:34.867 align:middle line:84%
You've got to figure
out what the hell you're

01:22:34.867 --> 01:22:36.270 align:middle line:90%
going to do every day.

01:22:36.270 --> 01:22:38.580 align:middle line:84%
So would it be fair
to say that you just

01:22:38.580 --> 01:22:41.280 align:middle line:84%
trade in one set of
responsibilities for another,

01:22:41.280 --> 01:22:43.480 align:middle line:84%
you don't absolve yourself
of responsibility?

01:22:43.480 --> 01:22:44.280 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yeah.

01:22:44.280 --> 01:22:46.633 align:middle line:90%
I mean, yeah.

01:22:46.633 --> 01:22:49.050 align:middle line:84%
I think there's a lot to think
about when you're out here.

01:22:49.050 --> 01:22:51.300 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we were just
in Seattle, and there's

01:22:51.300 --> 01:22:53.890 align:middle line:84%
nowhere to park that feels
really all that comfortable

01:22:53.890 --> 01:22:54.690 align:middle line:90%
in Seattle.

01:22:54.690 --> 01:22:56.148 align:middle line:84%
So you're in this
cool city and you

01:22:56.148 --> 01:22:58.530 align:middle line:84%
want to go explore, but then
where are you going to park?

01:22:58.530 --> 01:23:00.900 align:middle line:84%
So I think there's
just always things

01:23:00.900 --> 01:23:03.740 align:middle line:84%
that are on the back of your
mind when you're traveling.

01:23:03.740 --> 01:23:05.490 align:middle line:84%
You know, there are
tons of responsibility

01:23:05.490 --> 01:23:06.720 align:middle line:90%
that come with a van.

01:23:06.720 --> 01:23:10.170 align:middle line:84%
I think cleaning a van is
easier than cleaning a house,

01:23:10.170 --> 01:23:12.550 align:middle line:90%
but it's not like you just--

01:23:12.550 --> 01:23:16.080 align:middle line:84%
I don't think it's as
carefree, and doesn't free you

01:23:16.080 --> 01:23:19.170 align:middle line:84%
from some of the stresses
that you face in daily life.

01:23:19.170 --> 01:23:21.820 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, so I don't want to make
it seem like it's all negative.

01:23:21.820 --> 01:23:25.740 align:middle line:84%
I love the opportunities that
van life has presented me with.

01:23:25.740 --> 01:23:28.530 align:middle line:84%
But in terms of just kind
of thinking about some

01:23:28.530 --> 01:23:31.080 align:middle line:84%
of the challenges that maybe
you don't see on the internet

01:23:31.080 --> 01:23:33.360 align:middle line:84%
and that people aren't
always talking about,

01:23:33.360 --> 01:23:36.600 align:middle line:84%
and maybe what causes some
people to quit like a month

01:23:36.600 --> 01:23:38.640 align:middle line:84%
or two in that they
maybe didn't expect,

01:23:38.640 --> 01:23:41.430 align:middle line:84%
I think that's just some
of the causes I think,

01:23:41.430 --> 01:23:45.240 align:middle line:84%
that that may not sit well with
people once they're actually

01:23:45.240 --> 01:23:46.040 align:middle line:90%
out here.

01:23:46.040 --> 01:23:51.390 align:middle line:84%
>> Is van life here to stay, or
is it a trend that is fleeting?

01:23:51.390 --> 01:23:52.920 align:middle line:84%
>> I think van
life's here to stay.

01:23:52.920 --> 01:23:55.860 align:middle line:84%
I mean, people have been
doing it since way back when,

01:23:55.860 --> 01:23:58.110 align:middle line:84%
when people traveled
in VW buses.

01:23:58.110 --> 01:24:06.390 align:middle line:84%
And now I think it it's a more
accessible lifestyle to anyone.

01:24:06.390 --> 01:24:09.540 align:middle line:84%
Like, you don't have to be
a hippie living in a van

01:24:09.540 --> 01:24:10.650 align:middle line:90%
to live in a van now.

01:24:10.650 --> 01:24:13.500 align:middle line:84%
You can have a normal
job and maintain a career

01:24:13.500 --> 01:24:14.680 align:middle line:90%
from the road.

01:24:14.680 --> 01:24:17.250 align:middle line:84%
And so I think as more
and more people realize

01:24:17.250 --> 01:24:21.120 align:middle line:84%
that like, hey, I can
explore my career passions

01:24:21.120 --> 01:24:24.000 align:middle line:84%
and live in a van,
and it just, it

01:24:24.000 --> 01:24:26.460 align:middle line:84%
makes you able to think outside
the box a little bit more

01:24:26.460 --> 01:24:29.610 align:middle line:84%
in terms of the possibilities
for how you can make

01:24:29.610 --> 01:24:34.340 align:middle line:84%
money and still maintain your
freedom from a normal nine

01:24:34.340 --> 01:24:36.780 align:middle line:84%
to five job, and be able
to travel and work it

01:24:36.780 --> 01:24:41.160 align:middle line:84%
all together in a
nice, convenient way,

01:24:41.160 --> 01:24:45.350 align:middle line:90%
I think it's here to stay.

01:24:45.350 --> 01:24:48.278 align:middle line:90%
