01:24:56.090 --> 01:24:59.120 align:middle line:84%
>> In October, as our film
production started winding down

01:24:59.120 --> 01:25:01.640 align:middle line:84%
Kyleigh and I continued
reaching out to van people.

01:25:01.640 --> 01:25:03.955 align:middle line:84%
We formally interviewed
several new folks,

01:25:03.955 --> 01:25:05.330 align:middle line:84%
followed up on
Skype with friends

01:25:05.330 --> 01:25:07.247 align:middle line:84%
that we'd made over the
summer, and repeatedly

01:25:07.247 --> 01:25:09.740 align:middle line:84%
started up casual
conversations about van life

01:25:09.740 --> 01:25:11.150 align:middle line:90%
with strangers on the street.

01:25:11.150 --> 01:25:12.710 align:middle line:84%
These additional
dialogues confirmed

01:25:12.710 --> 01:25:13.940 align:middle line:90%
what we had already learned.

01:25:13.940 --> 01:25:16.250 align:middle line:84%
The majority of people
who come to live in a van

01:25:16.250 --> 01:25:19.880 align:middle line:84%
do so because A, the cost
of buying or renting a home

01:25:19.880 --> 01:25:22.100 align:middle line:84%
is a burden in today's
economy, and B,

01:25:22.100 --> 01:25:24.380 align:middle line:84%
people have the desire
to live adventurous lives

01:25:24.380 --> 01:25:26.900 align:middle line:84%
and travel more while
also putting a stronger

01:25:26.900 --> 01:25:29.840 align:middle line:84%
emphasis on experiences
instead of things.

01:25:29.840 --> 01:25:31.790 align:middle line:90%
I.e, being minimalists.

01:25:31.790 --> 01:25:34.220 align:middle line:84%
We also discovered that
reasons A and B are not

01:25:34.220 --> 01:25:36.770 align:middle line:84%
mutually exclusive,
meaning that more often

01:25:36.770 --> 01:25:39.710 align:middle line:84%
than not vanners come to van
because of both lower living

01:25:39.710 --> 01:25:42.650 align:middle line:84%
costs and the higher
likelihood for adventure.

01:25:42.650 --> 01:25:44.960 align:middle line:84%
It's also interesting to
note that at least one fifth

01:25:44.960 --> 01:25:47.090 align:middle line:84%
of the van lifers that
we interviewed in June,

01:25:47.090 --> 01:25:50.030 align:middle line:84%
July, August, and September
ended up selling their vans

01:25:50.030 --> 01:25:52.670 align:middle line:84%
and renting apartments,
remarking that van life wasn't

01:25:52.670 --> 01:25:54.080 align:middle line:90%
sustainable long-term.

01:25:54.080 --> 01:25:56.390 align:middle line:84%
While each party had their
own reasons and explanations

01:25:56.390 --> 01:25:58.640 align:middle line:84%
for why they stopped
van life, common threads

01:25:58.640 --> 01:25:59.580 align:middle line:90%
could be observed.

01:25:59.580 --> 01:26:01.760 align:middle line:84%
Ex-vanners explained that
while living in a van

01:26:01.760 --> 01:26:03.680 align:middle line:84%
offered certain
benefits, they ultimately

01:26:03.680 --> 01:26:06.800 align:middle line:84%
found it to be lonely and
craved community, namely friends

01:26:06.800 --> 01:26:10.940 align:middle line:84%
and family, missed their former
routines, stability, careers,

01:26:10.940 --> 01:26:13.280 align:middle line:84%
and lacked an overall
sense of purpose.

01:26:13.280 --> 01:26:15.380 align:middle line:84%
In our conversations
together Kyleigh and I

01:26:15.380 --> 01:26:18.470 align:middle line:84%
came to agree that van lifers
who tend to thrive on the road

01:26:18.470 --> 01:26:21.080 align:middle line:84%
full time and last past
the year and a half mark

01:26:21.080 --> 01:26:23.990 align:middle line:84%
are comprised of people who have
a deep love and appreciation

01:26:23.990 --> 01:26:25.010 align:middle line:90%
for the outdoors.

01:26:25.010 --> 01:26:27.410 align:middle line:84%
Such individuals tend to spend
the majority of their time

01:26:27.410 --> 01:26:29.660 align:middle line:84%
outside already, with
or without a van,

01:26:29.660 --> 01:26:31.880 align:middle line:84%
and thus thrive as
full time road warriors

01:26:31.880 --> 01:26:33.470 align:middle line:84%
once they acquire
a vehicle that's

01:26:33.470 --> 01:26:35.150 align:middle line:90%
conducive to their lifestyle.

01:26:35.150 --> 01:26:38.420 align:middle line:84%
As for the rest of us, van life
is a fantastic temporary break

01:26:38.420 --> 01:26:41.510 align:middle line:84%
from a stuffy desk job, a
reoccurring mortgage payment,

01:26:41.510 --> 01:26:44.060 align:middle line:84%
and a traditional,
sedentary lifestyle.

01:26:44.060 --> 01:26:46.670 align:middle line:84%
It's also a great way to
experience heaps of adventure

01:26:46.670 --> 01:26:48.790 align:middle line:84%
and see our country
for a year or two.

01:26:48.790 --> 01:26:51.440 align:middle line:84%
However, for most of
us, full time van life

01:26:51.440 --> 01:26:56.600 align:middle line:84%
seems to have big voids and is
not sustainable indefinitely.

01:26:56.600 --> 01:26:59.390 align:middle line:84%
Since June 2,
2018, Kyleigh and I

01:26:59.390 --> 01:27:02.540 align:middle line:84%
have traveled over 18,000 miles
while working on this film.

01:27:02.540 --> 01:27:04.580 align:middle line:84%
12,000 of those miles
were logged criss

01:27:04.580 --> 01:27:07.250 align:middle line:84%
crossing the Western United
States in our Sprinter van,

01:27:07.250 --> 01:27:10.220 align:middle line:84%
and 6,000 miles were covered
by airplane and rental car.

01:27:10.220 --> 01:27:12.230 align:middle line:84%
Over the span of
summer and fall we also

01:27:12.230 --> 01:27:15.080 align:middle line:84%
interviewed 40 plus
people in-depth about vans

01:27:15.080 --> 01:27:17.510 align:middle line:84%
and informally spoke
to at least 40 more.

01:27:17.510 --> 01:27:19.160 align:middle line:84%
Throughout our
conversations we learned

01:27:19.160 --> 01:27:21.170 align:middle line:84%
that vans are
increasing in popularity

01:27:21.170 --> 01:27:22.460 align:middle line:90%
for several different reasons.

01:27:22.460 --> 01:27:24.680 align:middle line:84%
And the first reason
is flexibility.

01:27:24.680 --> 01:27:27.380 align:middle line:84%
Vans are a complete
utilitarian package.

01:27:27.380 --> 01:27:30.260 align:middle line:84%
They are an RV, and a
truck, and a passenger car,

01:27:30.260 --> 01:27:31.190 align:middle line:90%
smashed into one.

01:27:31.190 --> 01:27:33.860 align:middle line:84%
Hence, vans offer their
owners complete control over

01:27:33.860 --> 01:27:35.480 align:middle line:84%
how they are
customized and used.

01:27:35.480 --> 01:27:38.000 align:middle line:84%
Do you want to start a mobile
acupuncture or chiropractor

01:27:38.000 --> 01:27:38.800 align:middle line:90%
business?

01:27:38.800 --> 01:27:40.190 align:middle line:90%
No problem, you can do that.

01:27:40.190 --> 01:27:42.920 align:middle line:84%
Do you have a big family and
want to see all 50 states?

01:27:42.920 --> 01:27:43.820 align:middle line:90%
Easy peasy.

01:27:43.820 --> 01:27:45.200 align:middle line:90%
And the list goes on and on.

01:27:45.200 --> 01:27:48.390 align:middle line:84%
Regardless of what your dream
is, if it requires a vehicle

01:27:48.390 --> 01:27:49.580 align:middle line:90%
a van fits that bill.

01:27:49.580 --> 01:27:51.590 align:middle line:90%
Secondly, vans are economical.

01:27:51.590 --> 01:27:53.900 align:middle line:84%
As the cost of living
continues to increase,

01:27:53.900 --> 01:27:55.940 align:middle line:84%
many people choose
to or are forced

01:27:55.940 --> 01:27:58.340 align:middle line:84%
to get creative about how
they exist on this earth.

01:27:58.340 --> 01:28:00.530 align:middle line:84%
Vans are a viable
solution because they

01:28:00.530 --> 01:28:02.930 align:middle line:84%
enable folks to maintain
a high standard of life

01:28:02.930 --> 01:28:04.460 align:middle line:90%
without the homeless stigma.

01:28:04.460 --> 01:28:07.190 align:middle line:84%
By skipping a traditional
home and moving into a gas

01:28:07.190 --> 01:28:10.590 align:middle line:84%
efficient mini bus, van dwellers
can save thousands of dollars

01:28:10.590 --> 01:28:11.390 align:middle line:90%
every month.

01:28:11.390 --> 01:28:13.160 align:middle line:84%
This in turn takes a
lot of the pressure

01:28:13.160 --> 01:28:15.830 align:middle line:84%
away from having to bust
your hump at a job you hate.

01:28:15.830 --> 01:28:18.422 align:middle line:84%
When life costs less,
you have to work less.

01:28:18.422 --> 01:28:19.880 align:middle line:84%
And when you have
to work less, you

01:28:19.880 --> 01:28:22.700 align:middle line:84%
have a lot more free time to
do that which makes you happy.

01:28:22.700 --> 01:28:25.490 align:middle line:84%
Thirdly, vans offer
people freedom.

01:28:25.490 --> 01:28:28.520 align:middle line:84%
And freedom, as we all know, is
heavily prized in our culture.

01:28:28.520 --> 01:28:30.620 align:middle line:84%
For some people, freedom
equals liberation

01:28:30.620 --> 01:28:33.860 align:middle line:84%
from bills and the 40 hour
work week, which ties directly

01:28:33.860 --> 01:28:37.010 align:middle line:84%
into the point that I just made
about vans being economical.

01:28:37.010 --> 01:28:40.490 align:middle line:84%
But for others, freedom has
more to do with spontaneity

01:28:40.490 --> 01:28:42.590 align:middle line:84%
and adventure, and
vans are just as good

01:28:42.590 --> 01:28:45.500 align:middle line:84%
as spontaneity and adventure
as they are at saving money.

01:28:45.500 --> 01:28:47.510 align:middle line:84%
When you hit the road
in a decked out van,

01:28:47.510 --> 01:28:50.100 align:middle line:84%
you never have to book a
hotel or make a reservation

01:28:50.100 --> 01:28:50.900 align:middle line:90%
at a restaurant.

01:28:50.900 --> 01:28:53.640 align:middle line:84%
You can decide to stay somewhere
for an extra day or leave a day

01:28:53.640 --> 01:28:54.440 align:middle line:90%
earlier.

01:28:54.440 --> 01:28:57.023 align:middle line:84%
And you get to bring the comfort
of your home wherever you go.

01:28:57.023 --> 01:28:59.180 align:middle line:84%
A van is like a turtle
shell, providing you

01:28:59.180 --> 01:29:02.360 align:middle line:84%
with most of your necessities
wherever and whenever

01:29:02.360 --> 01:29:03.180 align:middle line:90%
you need them.

01:29:03.180 --> 01:29:05.663 align:middle line:84%
And if this isn't freedom,
I don't know what is.

01:29:05.663 --> 01:29:07.580 align:middle line:84%
At the beginning of this
project Kyleigh and I

01:29:07.580 --> 01:29:09.890 align:middle line:84%
set out to determine
why vans are booming.

01:29:09.890 --> 01:29:12.200 align:middle line:84%
I think we were
successful in this venture

01:29:12.200 --> 01:29:15.260 align:middle line:84%
and determined that vans are
trending for the three reasons

01:29:15.260 --> 01:29:16.280 align:middle line:90%
that I just discussed.

01:29:16.280 --> 01:29:18.650 align:middle line:84%
Flexibility,
economy, and freedom.

01:29:18.650 --> 01:29:22.580 align:middle line:84%
As for whether or not vans are
the new American dream, for me

01:29:22.580 --> 01:29:23.900 align:middle line:90%
the jury's still out.

01:29:23.900 --> 01:29:25.670 align:middle line:84%
Maybe they are,
maybe they're not.

01:29:25.670 --> 01:29:27.260 align:middle line:84%
What is the American
dream anyway?

01:29:27.260 --> 01:29:28.730 align:middle line:90%
Is it the white picket fence?

01:29:28.730 --> 01:29:31.910 align:middle line:84%
Is it the husband and wife,
or the 2.5 kid family?

01:29:31.910 --> 01:29:35.000 align:middle line:84%
After pondering on this
concept for many months

01:29:35.000 --> 01:29:38.180 align:middle line:84%
I've come to realize that the
idea of any one thing being

01:29:38.180 --> 01:29:40.310 align:middle line:84%
the American dream
is preposterous.

01:29:40.310 --> 01:29:44.200 align:middle line:84%
There are roughly 300 million
people in the US alone,

01:29:44.200 --> 01:29:47.540 align:middle line:84%
and each one of those people has
their own unique idea of what

01:29:47.540 --> 01:29:49.040 align:middle line:90%
their dreams and wants are.

01:29:49.040 --> 01:29:51.500 align:middle line:84%
Sure, some people want a more
traditional cookie cutter

01:29:51.500 --> 01:29:54.080 align:middle line:84%
lifestyle, but others
rebel against this

01:29:54.080 --> 01:29:55.700 align:middle line:84%
and strive for an
existence that's

01:29:55.700 --> 01:29:56.990 align:middle line:90%
unique to their own values.

01:29:56.990 --> 01:29:58.340 align:middle line:90%
And van life is no different.

01:29:58.340 --> 01:30:01.130 align:middle line:84%
For some people
exploring the US in a van

01:30:01.130 --> 01:30:03.620 align:middle line:84%
seems like an
idyllic, fun endeavor.

01:30:03.620 --> 01:30:05.420 align:middle line:84%
But for others this
type of lifestyle

01:30:05.420 --> 01:30:08.960 align:middle line:84%
probably seems irresponsible,
claustrophobic, and dreadful.

01:30:08.960 --> 01:30:10.520 align:middle line:84%
And there's absolutely
nothing wrong

01:30:10.520 --> 01:30:12.020 align:middle line:90%
with either of these stances.

01:30:12.020 --> 01:30:14.780 align:middle line:84%
It's ultimately up to
the individual, to you,

